latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This is the story of Ushaben Sutaria from New York who experienced Pramukh Swami Maharaj's compassion firsthand. Pramukh Swami Maharaj's compassion wasn't showered simply at the sight of someone's sorrow. It was more than that. The ancient sages call it "akaran daya". Through his personal meetings, letters and house-to-house visits, Pramukh Swami's compassion saved and pacified countless individuals.

His care and concern for all beings were evident through his active support for the victims of natural calamities, his involvement in de-addiction drives, his 760,000 letters written to those seeking guidance, regardless of caste, creed, culture, or geographical boundaries.

#PramukhSwami100 #InspiredbyPSM

“In the joy of others lies our own, 
In the progress of others rests our own, In the good of others abides our own, Know this to be the key to peace and happiness.”

These were not simply words spoken by Pramukh Swami Maharaj, but rather his life motto. It was through his thoughts, words, and actions that he inspired young and old alike to selflessly serve others.

#PramukhSwami100 #InspiredbyPSM

Pramukh Swami Maharaj lived his life in the service of others. His service was selfless, in all ways, and he inspired countless others to do the same. 

Dr. Vijayeta Rangarajan was a volunteer in the BAPS Bhuj earthquake medical relief camp. After seeing Pramukh Swami Maharaj for the first time during her trip to Bhuj, she was motivated to incorporate the teachings of Pramukh Swami Maharaj - to serve others by giving herself thoroughly in her professional and personal life.

#PramukhSwami100
#InspiredbyPSM

One of the worst dam failures in history. 25,000 casualties. This was the Macchhu Dam flood in Morbi, Gujarat.

When Pramukh Swami Maharaj came to know of this dam failure, he asked young volunteers to travel to Morbi immediately to serve. The volunteers got to work right away. Pramukh Swami instructed them to arrange for chai in addition to water. Why? Because he recognized that as vital as the residents’ need for water was, a need for homely comfort in chai provided a glimmer of hope for normalcy.

In just a few days, Pramukh Swami himself arrived in Morbi, stepping through mud and debris, consoling the victims, and inspiring volunteers. He had an unwavering commitment such that where one sees suffering, one stands by it and makes it one’s own, regardless of how difficult it is. For Pramukh Swami Maharaj, where there was pain, there was an opportunity to soothe; where there was sadness, there was an opportunity to love; where there was a need, there was an opportunity to give; where there was injustice, there was an opportunity to act. Even today, his silent spirituality and selfless service serve as a model for all.

Equal Love for all.

Life Lessons #pramukhswami100 #psm100 #baps

In a time of busy schedules and clashing personalities, Pramukh Swami Maharaj introduced a concept that keeps the home intact - ghar sabha, a dedicated family time enriched with spirituality and fun.  Ghar sabha breaks down walls of misunderstandings, bridges generation gaps and empowers families with love, understanding and spirituality. 

Make this International Day of Families the beginning of stronger bonds.

#internationaldayoffamilies

We sincerely thank our 100,000 followers who have joined us on our journey to learn from the values, traditions, and beliefs of BAPS and the lineage of gurus. Please do continue to share the joy. 

#BAPS
#PramukhSwami
#MahantSwami

Pramukh Swami Maharaj has inspired countless people to incorporate his life’s example of humility into their own lives.

Please share an inspiration or an incident from your own life using #PramukhSwami100 #PSM100 #InspiredbyPSM

Comment below on how you have tried to remain humble in your life.

Sapna Patel was influenced by Pramukh Swami’s humility to selflessly serve our country as a United States Army Veteran.

Puja Patel - a mother, daughter, sister, and wife - has been influenced by Pramukh Swami’s humility in providing for others. She takes from his example in showing the future generation the importance of living a life of modesty.

Hemali Patel was influenced by Pramukh Swami’s humility in helping others. As a neurologist, her humble and sincere nature in treating her patients has made her a well-respected physician and leader in the community.

Shailja Brahmbhatt, a teacher and role model for the next generation, was profoundly influenced by Pramukh Swami’s humble ability to build strong and meaningful relationships, something she has nurtured with her students and colleagues.

Let's celebrate Pramukh Swami Maharaj’s centennial by sharing our experiences!

One of the best ways to honor his life is to celebrate his virtues!

One virtue that resonated with everyone was his profound humility, also described in the Shreemad Bhagwat as “anaham-kruti.”

Share your story of how his humility has impacted you & your life.

#PramukhSwami100
#PSM100
#InspiredbyPSM

Discover the first traditional Hindu mandir in Paris where Indian craftsmanship meets French ingenuity 🇮🇳🇫🇷

A sacred space for peace, reflection and devotion is rising in the heart of France, a dream nurtured for over 50 years, now coming to life through the unwavering dedication and spiritual guidance of His Holiness Mahant Swami Maharaj.

Visit the link in @bapsparis bio to watch the full video.

On the 133rd birth anniversary of His Holiness Yogiji Maharaj, let's reflect on his timeless wisdom, dedication to humanity, and his belief in future generations. His teachings inspire us to stay connected to our roots and traditions, no matter where we are.

Yogiji Maharaj ki Jay!

#YogijiMaharaj

Prayers for Pahalgam

BAPS condemns the brutal terrorist attack in Pahalgam, Jammu & Kashmir, India.

His Holiness Mahant Swami Maharaj and BAPS worldwide continue to pray for the innocent victims and their families, and for the recovery of the injured. 

We also pray that in this hour of deep grief and shock, may the whole world unite to take conscious and collective action to uproot terrorism everywhere and anywhere in the world.

latestPosts.caption:
Vice President of the United States Visits Swaminarayan Akshardham, New Delhi

New Delhi, 21 April 2025 – The Vice President of the United States, JD Vance, along with his wife, Second Lady Usha Vance, and their children—Ewan, Vivek, and Mirabel—visited Swaminarayan Akshardham in New Delhi as the first stop of his maiden official visit to India.

The Vance family explored the mandir’s majestic art and architecture, experiencing India’s heritage and cultural depth. They appreciated the messages of harmony, family values, and timeless wisdom embodied in the Akshardham campus.

The visit symbolizes the shared values of faith, peace, and unity that continue to strengthen ties between India and the United States.

Vice President Vance was presented a personal letter of blessings and prayers from His Holiness Mahant Swami Maharaj. The letter expressed heartfelt gratitude for the visit and special prayers for the well-being of the Vice President and his family, as well as for the continued unity and progress of the United States of America.

As a gesture of friendship, the Vance family was presented with several commemorative gifts, including a model of the Swaminarayan Akshardham mandir, intricately carved wooden elephants, literature about the Swaminarayan Akshardham campuses in New Delhi and Robbinsville (USA), and value-based illustrated storybooks for their children. A framed family photograph taken in front of the mandir was also presented as a special memento.

Sharing his experience in the guest book, US Vice President JD Vance  wrote:

“Thank you all so much for your hospitality and kindness in welcoming me and my family to this beautiful place. It is a great credit to India that you built a beautiful temple with precision and care. Our kids, in particular, loved it. God bless.”

#USIndiaRelations @vp @slotus #usindiadosti
#BAPS #Akshardham
